89
00:06:11,137 --> 00:06:14,941
My lame food earned me a Michelin star.

90
00:06:15,608 --> 00:06:19,412
<i>He is playing the part of a young chef
working at a top-class hotel.</i>

91
00:06:22,882 --> 00:06:27,253
<i>Tamamori started acting on TV shows
and in movies ten years ago.</i>

92
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:32,091
<i>We learn of his policy for acting
during a break between scenes.</i>

93
00:06:35,995 --> 00:06:40,032
<i>He is holding a box of vegetables,
which are props.</i>

94
00:06:41,367 --> 00:06:44,404
Not yet. We're not filming yet.

95
00:06:44,470 --> 00:06:46,072
It's fine. Let's do it.

96
00:06:46,739 --> 00:06:49,475
Someone take this.
Don't make him carry such heavy props.

97
00:06:51,677 --> 00:06:53,346
It's fine. I got them.

98
00:06:53,413 --> 00:06:56,582
You'll tire yourself out.

99
00:06:58,317 --> 00:07:00,253
